---
/**
 * FAQ — native <details>/<summary>, CSS-only styling.
 * Design doc §6 interaction rules.
 */
import Container from "./Container.astro";
import Section from "./Section.astro";
import TextBlock from "./TextBlock.astro";
---

<Section>
  <Container>
    <TextBlock align="center">
      <h2>Questions developers ask.</h2>
    </TextBlock>

    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Does InferBridge store my prompts?</summary>
        <p>
          No. We log metadata only &mdash; tokens, latency, cost,
          provider, request ID. Prompt and completion content are never
          written to logs. There&rsquo;s a dedicated test in the codebase
          that fails if anyone tries to change this.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What happens if InferBridge goes down?</summary>
        <p>
          Revert the two lines. Your SDK talks directly to OpenAI again
          in seconds. No data migration. No lock-in.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How is this different from OpenRouter or Portkey?</summary>
        <p>
          BYOK by default &mdash; you pay providers directly, we take no
          cut. Indian providers (Sarvam, self-hosted) are first-class,
          not an afterthought. And we&rsquo;re built for developers who
          want simple, debuggable routing, not an enterprise policy engine.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What about tool calling, vision, and embeddings?</summary>
        <p>
          Streaming tool use and vision aren&rsquo;t hardened yet &mdash;
          use the provider SDK directly for those. Embeddings aren&rsquo;t
          exposed through InferBridge at all in v1. Text chat completions,
          streaming, caching, and fallback are production-ready.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Is my data safe?</summary>
        <p>
          Provider API keys are Fernet-encrypted at rest, decrypted only
          in-memory at request time. We never log content. You can delete
          any registered key from <code>/v1/keys</code> at any time.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I export an audit log for DPDP / GDPR?</summary>
        <p>
          Yes. <code>GET /v1/audit/export</code> returns a signed report
          (JSON or PDF) of every request the caller has made over a
          window of up to 90 days, with a SHA-256 signature so the
          artefact stays verifiable after it leaves InferBridge. Only
          metadata &mdash; provider, model, tokens, cost, residency
          &mdash; is included; prompts and completions are never stored
          and therefore never exported.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I self-host InferBridge?</summary>
        <p>
          Not publicly yet. Open-source release is planned for month 2.
          Email
          <a href="mailto:hello@inferbridge.dev">hello@inferbridge.dev</a>
          if you want early access or need an on-prem deployment.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Section>

<style>
  h2 {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .faq {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  details {
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--gray-700);
  }

  details:first-child {
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--gray-700);
  }

  summary {
    padding: 20px 16px 20px 8px;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--gray-50);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: var(--fs-body);
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  summary::before {
    content: "›";
    color: var(--accent-text);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1;
    transition: transform var(--transition);
  }

  details[open] > summary::before {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  summary:hover {
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }

  details p {
    color: var(--gray-300);
    font-size: var(--fs-body-sm);
    line-height: var(--lh-body-sm);
    padding: 0 16px 20px 38px;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  details code {
    background-color: var(--gray-800);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--accent-text);
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  details a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
